d_at": "2018-10-05T23:17:46Z", "closed_at": "2018-10-05T23:17:46Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/21183", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21183", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21183.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21183.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>logits that are -inf will be given 0 probability and logits that are<br>\ninf will result in a nan output. Likewise if all logits are -inf the<br>\noutput will also be nan.</p>\n<p>This is done by using where operators, mostly because <code>0 * inf = nan</code><br>\nand <code>x/0 = sign(x) inf</code> following the IEEE 754 standard. However these<br>\nresults are not mathematically correct in the context of the sparsemax<br>\nalgorithm.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #15564.\">Fixes</span>: <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"284010225\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/15564\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/15564/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/15564\">#15564</a></p>", "body_text": "logits that are -inf will be given 0 probability and logits that are\ninf will result in a nan output. Likewise if all logits are -inf the\noutput will also be nan.\nThis is done by using where operators, mostly because 0 * inf = nan\nand x/0 = sign(x) inf following the IEEE 754 standard. However these\nresults are not mathematically correct in the context of the sparsemax\nalgorithm.\nFixes: #15564", "body": "logits that are -inf will be given 0 probability and logits that are\r\ninf will result in a nan output. Likewise if all logits are -inf the\r\noutput will also be nan.\r\n\r\nThis is done by using where operators, mostly because `0 * inf = nan`\r\nand `x/0 = sign(x) inf` following the IEEE 754 standard. However these\r\nresults are not mathematically correct in the context of the sparsemax\r\nalgorithm.\r\n\r\nFixes: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/15564"}